2ec644220115729a1a6938e7093e2e8ea87ebca0.commit.message:
Some changes to how Validators are used
 - The processors do not now set default Validators, if the RequestData does not supply a Validator instance, then no validation is done
 - Added a tag to WSSecurityEngineResult to indicate whether the token was validated or not
 - Added support for the use-case of a Signature KeyInfo pointing to a BinarySecurityToken, which has been validated by a custom validator. Trust verification will pass for this case.
2ec644220115729a1a6938e7093e2e8ea87ebca0.commit.author.name: Colm O hEigeartaigh

c4d48331baeb8e63de788228879fe60da28cf964.commit.message:
Some changes to the Validators
 - Added a TAG_TRANSFORMED_TOKEN tag to WSSecurityEngineResult to represent a transformed token from the Validators, and added support for it in the processors
 - Separated signature trust verification in the SamlAssertionValidator to allow subclassing.
c4d48331baeb8e63de788228879fe60da28cf964.commit.author.name: Colm O hEigeartaigh
